In response to the nationwide strike called by the All-India Bank Employeesâ€™ Association (AIBEA) against the alleged unfair policies of the State Bank of India (SBI) towards the employees of its associate banks, the employees of associate banks here remained off the work on Friday.The bank employees staged a demonstration before the main branch of the State Bank of Mysore (SBM) here.The protesters alleged that the management of SBI was meting out a step-motherly treatment towards the employees of its five subsidiary banks comprising SBM, State Bank of Bikaner and Jaipur, State Bank of Patiala, State Bank of Travancore and State Bank of Hyderabad. The protesters condemned the move to impose service conditions and rules related to career progression of SBI on the employees of associate banks.They demanded de-linking of associate banks from SBI.The services in associate banks of SBI were disrupted owing to the strike.